{"id": "post_deleg_alpha_neg_zero", "category": "alpha_edges", "rationale": "sub(x, y, alpha=-0.0): per IEEE 754, -(-0.0) = +0.0, so add_scaled(a,b,+0.0); +0.0*y = +0.0 with NaN propagation rules. For finite x and finite y, should yield x. Verify sub_scaled doesn't FTZ alpha=-0.0.", "args_spec": [{"kind": "tensor", "shape": [4], "dtype": "float32", "data": [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0], "fill": null, "transform": "none", "transform_args": {}}, {"kind": "tensor", "shape": [4], "dtype": "float32", "data": [10.0, 20.0, 30.0, 40.0], "fill": null, "transform": "none", "transform_args": {}}], "kwargs": {"alpha": -0.0}, "autograd_check": false}
